    <h2>üìñ Key Concepts</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Management Information Systems (MIS):</strong> Systems that support decision-making, coordination, control, analysis, and visualization of data in organizations.</li>
      <li><strong>Strategic Business Objectives:</strong> Operational excellence, new products/services, customer intimacy, improved decision-making, competitive advantage, and survival.</li>
      <li><strong>Information System Components:</strong> Input, Processing, Output, and Feedback.</li>
      <li><strong>Dimensions:</strong> Organizations, Management, and Technology.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>üåç Globalization and MIS</h2>
    <p>Information systems enable a flattened world‚Äîbusinesses compete and collaborate globally, operate 24/7, and transform how products are delivered and managed through digital platforms.</p>

    <h2>üîÆ Digital Firms</h2>
    <p>Digital firms accomplish core processes through digital networks and manage corporate assets digitally, offering flexibility in time and space (e.g., remote work, global coordination).</p>

